<h1>Using an SSL Terminating Reverse Proxy with Passenger</h1>

An SSL terminating reverse proxy is simply a web server that is configured to accept encrypted https requests from clients, and to forward them as unencrypted http requests to another backend process, and to relay the unencrypted results from the backend process back to the client via the encrypted channel. In our case the backend process will be Passenger running on the same host. Setting up an SSL terminating reverse proxy is super easy, and this article will walk you through how to do it.

## Prepare the system

Follow [these instructions](<%= url_for "/deploy/#{locals[:integration_mode_type]}/reverse_proxy.html" %>), before continuing with this guide.

Assumptions: you are using the bash shell, and have admin rights to your computer, and are using a modern browser. Ensure that OpenSSL is installed.

